    <briefdescription>
<para>Streaming CBOR encoder — zero-alloc, caller-provided buffer. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Encodes CBOR (RFC 8949) items into a fixed buffer. No heap, no recursion, no indefinite-length items. Map and array sizes must be known before writing begins.</para>
<para>Supported types: unsigned int, signed int, float32, bool, null, text string, byte string, array, map.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage — sensor telemetry with integer keys</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/>buf[32];</highlight></codeline>
